{"cursor":"3639","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{Infobox scientist |name = Charles Chamberland |image =Charles Chamberland.jpg\n|image_size =220px |caption = Charles Chamberland |birth_date = March 12, 1851\n|birth_place = Chilly-le-Vignoble |death_date = May 2, 1908 |death_place =\n|residence = |citizenship = |nationality = France |ethnicity = |field =\nmicrobiology |work_institutions = |alma_mater = |doctoral_advisor =\n|doctoral_students = |known_for = Chamberland filter |author_abbrev_bot\n=|author_abbrev_zoo = |influences = Pasteur |influenced = |prizes = |religion =\n|footnotes = |signature = }}'Charles Chamberland' (12 March 1851 â 2 May 1908)\nwas a French microbiologist from Chilly-le-Vignoble in the department of Jura\nwho worked with Louis Pasteur.\n\nIn 1884 he developed a type of filtration known today as the Chamberland filter\nor Chamberland-Pasteur filter, a device that made use of an unglazed porcelain\nbar. The filter had pores that were smaller than\nbacteria, thus making it possible to pass a solution containing bacteria through\nthe filter, and having the bacteria completely removed from the solution. He was\nalso credited for starting a research project that led to the invention of the\nautoclave device in 1879.\n\nHe worked with Pasteur and came up, by chance, with a vaccine for chicken\ncholera. He went away on holiday, forgetting to inject the disease into some\nchickens as he had been told. When he came back he saw the jar of bacteria\nsitting on the side and thought he would inject it into the chickens anyway. To\nhis amazement they did not die. He reported this to Pasteur, who told him to\ninject a fresh form into the chickens, they still did not die. He then went on\nto injecting the fresh form into new chickens, they did die. {{cite journal\n|last=Norn |first=Svend |authorlink= |coauthors=Kruse Poul R, Kruse Edith\n|year=2006|month= |title=On the history of injection |journal=Dansk\nmedicinhistorisk Ã¥rbog |volume=34 |issue= |pages=104â13 |publisher= |location =\nDenmark| issn = 0084-9588| pmid = 17526154\n| bibcode = | oclc =| id = | url = | language = | format = | accessdate = |\n| laysummary = | laysource = | laydate = | quote =\n }} He had found a vaccine. They had also discovered that a weakened form\n of a disease can act as a vaccine.\n","linknr":139,"url":"Charles_Chamberland","recorded":1376417281,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Charles_Chamberland&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Charles_Chamberland&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Charles_Chamberland","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.visualEditor.viewPageTarget.noscript&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/File:Charles_Chamberland.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9a/Charles_Chamberland.jpg/220px-Charles_Chamberland.jpg","/wiki/Chilly-le-Vignoble","/wiki/France","/wiki/Microbiology","/wiki/Chamberland_filter","/wiki/Pasteur","/wiki/Microbiologist","/wiki/Chilly-le-Vignoble","/wiki/Jura_(department)","/wiki/Pasteur","/wiki/Chamberland_filter","/wiki/Porcelain","#cite_note-Horzinek_1997-1","/wiki/Bacteria","/wiki/Autoclave","/wiki/Vaccine","/wiki/Chicke